### StudExE4 Driver Service API Tests
### This file follows the flow: User Service Registration -> Driver Service Linking

@gatewayUrl = http://localhost:8080
@userServiceUrl = http://localhost:8081
@driverServiceUrl = http://localhost:8082
@phone = 628123456789

### STEP 1: Register/Check User in User Service
# This happens first when the bot identifies a new phone number.
POST {{userServiceUrl}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone": "{{phone}}"
}

### STEP 2: Get User ID
# We need the MongoDB _id from the User service to link the driver.
GET {{userServiceUrl}}/users/{{phone}}

### STEP 3: Create/Link Driver in Driver Service
# Use the "id" from the previous response as "user_id" here.
POST {{driverServiceUrl}}/drivers/auth
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone": "{{phone}}",
    "user_id": "PASTE_USER_ID_HERE"
}

### STEP 4: Admin Completes Driver Data (Manual CRUD)
# Fill in Vehicle Type and Plate Number to "Verify" the driver.
PUT {{driverServiceUrl}}/drivers/me?phone={{phone}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Driver",
    "display_name": "John D.",
    "vehicle_type": "Bike",
    "plate_number": "B 1234 ABC"
}

### STEP 5: Toggle Online Status (Used by Bot !on/!off)
PUT {{driverServiceUrl}}/drivers/me/status?phone={{phone}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "is_online": true
}

### STEP 6: Get Driver Info
GET {{driverServiceUrl}}/drivers/me?phone={{phone}}
